column5: Well this morning i headed out to meet my nephew to do some ice fishing at one of his spots the day started out slow and staid that way most of the day the winds where blowing good but we did manage to get two fish  i had to let Ryan hold them due to the fact he got skunked  so we took one each when i got it home to clean this is what it had in it's belly  i am surprised it had any more room for the minnow it took  rob
YUMMMM.. Pickeral and a bonus Perch snack!  Thanks for the post/pics.

Nice eye's.  It's amazing what they'll cram down the gullet and then still hit something else.  They're oportunistic feeders and when instinct says "that's food" they react.  I caught a big pike this spring that had 4" of tail sticking out its throat.
Wow, that's pretty cool.  Take it as a sign of a year of 'plenty' to come.

Well I had heard word you did good today.The wife couldnt wait to call me at WORK. I must say I am surprised you only got the two.  Ryan does have the spot to fish there,just a matter of time before he nails them too.  Great job Bro.  You look very cool in Orange.   Wayne clean your glass,s,those are WALLEYE.
that was a pretty cool report.  love the surprise while cleaning the fish!  Cheers!
Well Brian I think Wayne said it right you just read it too fast.  Congrats on those nice eater size Walleye
Nope! Two inches shorter and they'd be Pickeral, those are definately Wall-ice!  Great report and pics!!!   How come everybody can catch fish except MTP?
Nothing like kicking the poor guy when he,s down.LOL It was funny though.
